issue.title: Android UX interactions - Select
issue.body:
Create a gesture where you can move a selected object.  
- You should be able to click it once to select it
- Tapping outside the object releases the selection
- Selection should be in scope for other UX interactions.

issue.title: Android Wrapper of Path Object for UX Interactions
issue.body:
Currently we draw the resulting object directly onto the environment.  We instead want to store the object as some kind of object which can be re-sized, moved, and color changed.

In our Android drawing framework, find how they define objects like these.  Change how we currently draw new objects so that they include this class wrapper.  

Just complete the upcasting; don't worry about implementing re-size, rotate, move, etc.

issue.title: Android generate a shape

milestone.title: First Goal
milestone.description:
A working classifier which places perfect-shaped objects in a drawing environment.

Minimally Viable Product.

issue.body:
Given points denoting two opposing corners of a region, a label identifying the shape type, and the original user path data, generate a perfect shape in these coordinates.

square and circle (as well as ellipses and rectange) can be determined simply from the opposing corner bounds.

line must query the path origin and path destination.
